Mozambique to Build $1.5 Billion Coal Terminal, State Radio Station Says

-- B y   F r e d   K a t e r e r e
-- 
2011-07-05T03:31:31Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-05/mozambique-to-build-1-5-billion-coal-terminal-state-radio-station-says.html
Mozambique will construct a coal
terminal valued at $1.5 billion at the northern Nacala port,
state controlled Radio Mocambique reported, citing Rosario
Mualeia, chairman of the national ports and railway utility.  To contact the reporter on this story:
